#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.multinomial.rst:4
msgid "numpy.random.Generator.multinomial"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.multinomial.rst:8
msgid "method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:2
msgid "Draw samples from a multinomial distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:4
msgid ""
"The multinomial distribution is a multivariate generalization of the "
"binomial distribution.  Take an experiment with one of ``p`` possible "
"outcomes.  An example of such an experiment is throwing a dice, where the "
"outcome can be 1 through 6.  Each sample drawn from the distribution "
"represents `n` such experiments.  Its values, ``X_i = [X_0, X_1, ..., "
"X_p]``, represent the number of times the outcome was ``i``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:15
msgid "**n**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:-1
msgid "int or array-like of ints"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:15
msgid "Number of experiments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:23
msgid "**pvals**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:-1
msgid "array-like of floats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:18
msgid ""
"Probabilities of each of the ``p`` different outcomes with shape ``(k0, "
"k1, ..., kn, p)``. Each element ``pvals[i,j,...,:]`` must sum to 1 (however, "
"the last element is always assumed to account for the remaining probability, "
"as long as ``sum(pvals[..., :-1], axis=-1) <= 1.0``. Must have at least 1 "
"dimension where pvals.shape[-1] > 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:35
msgid "**size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:-1
msgid "int or tuple of ints, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:26
msgid ""
"Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., ``(m, n, k)``, then ``m * n * "
"k`` samples are drawn each with ``p`` elements. Default is None where the "
"output size is determined by the broadcast shape of ``n`` and all by the "
"final dimension of ``pvals``, which is denoted as ``b=(b0, b1, ..., bq)``. "
"If size is not None, then it must be compatible with the broadcast shape "
"``b``. Specifically, size must have ``q`` or more elements and size[-(q-j):] "
"must equal ``bj``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:57
msgid "**out**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:-1
msgid "ndarray"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:40
msgid ""
"The drawn samples, of shape size, if provided. When size is provided, the "
"output shape is size + (p,)  If not specified, the shape is determined by "
"the broadcast shape of ``n`` and ``pvals``, ``(b0, b1, ..., bq)`` augmented "
"with the dimension of the multinomial, ``p``, so that that output shape is "
"``(b0, b1, ..., bq, p)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.multinomial:47
msgid ""
"Each entry ``out[i,j,...,:]`` is a ``p``-dimensional value drawn from the "
"distribution."
msgstr ""

